  "source": "Theorem:\ngiven: k, m, n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nthen:\n. \\sum:of{\\sum:of{k}:and{m}}:and{n} = \\sum:of{k}:and{\\sum:of{m}:and{n}}\n. \\sum:of{m}:and{n} = \\sum:of{n}:and{m}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Addition is associative and commutative: for all $k, m, n \\in \\omega$, $(k + m) + n = k + (m + n)$ and $m + n = n + m$. Both are proved by induction using the recursive definition of addition.\"\nId: \"ff7967ab-f54e-4124-bb1b-e74888d23635\"",
